## 4. Feature Specifications

### 4.1 Job Fetchers

#### 4.1.1 Indeed Fetcher (via JSearch API on RapidAPI)

- **API:** `https://jsearch.p.rapidapi.com/search`
- **Free tier:** 500 requests/month
- **Queries per run:** 4 (limited to conserve quota)
- **Filters:** Country = Germany, date_posted = week
- **Delay between requests:** 500ms

#### 4.1.2 LinkedIn Fetcher (via SerpAPI Google Jobs)

- **API:** `https://serpapi.com/search.json` with `engine=google_jobs`
- **Free tier:** 100 searches/month
- **Queries per run:** 3 (limited to conserve quota)
- **Filters:** Location = Munich, Bavaria, Germany, date_posted = week
- **Delay between requests:** 600ms

#### 4.1.3 StepStone Fetcher (SerpAPI + Direct Fallback)

- **Primary:** SerpAPI Google Jobs filtered to `site:stepstone.de`
- **Fallback:** Direct HTTP fetch of StepStone search results, parsing JSON-LD structured data
- **Queries per run:** 2
- **Filters:** Location = Munich, radius = 30km, age = 7 days
- **Delay between requests:** 600-800ms

#### 4.1.4 Deduplication

Jobs are deduplicated by `platform + external_id` before insertion. Existing jobs with status `new` get their match score and description updated; jobs with any other status are not overwritten.

### 4.2 Profile Matcher

Scoring algorithm (0-100 scale):

| Factor | Max Points | Logic |
|--------|-----------|-------|
| Primary skills match | 40 | 5 points per matched skill |
| Role title match | 20 | Exact target role match |
| Title keywords | 10 | 3 points per keyword (senior, lead, flutter, etc.) |
| Secondary skills match | 15 | 2 points per matched skill |
| Location match | 10 | Remote=10, Munich onsite=10, Germany hybrid=7 |
| Bonus keywords | 10 | 2 points per keyword (fintech, mobile, startup, etc.) |
| Seniority match | 5 | Contains "senior" or "10+ years" |
| Negative keywords | -15 each | junior, intern, php, wordpress, etc. |

**Minimum threshold:** 15 points (jobs below this are discarded).

### 4.3 Cron Job

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/jobs/cron`
- **Schedule:** Every 4 hours (`0 */4 * * *`)
- **Max duration:** 60 seconds
- **Authentication:** `CRON_SECRET` bearer token (Vercel sends this automatically)
- **Flow:**
  1. Fetch jobs from all 3 platforms in parallel
  2. Match and rank against profile (minimum score: 15)
  3. Upsert into Supabase (skip existing non-`new` jobs)
  4. Log the run to `cron_logs`
  5. Return stats JSON

### 4.4 Authentication

- **Method:** Password-based with HTTP-only cookie session
- **Password source:** `admin_password` environment variable (already exists)
- **Session duration:** 7 days
- **Token:** SHA-256 hash stored in cookie + server-side Set
- **Endpoints:**
  - `POST /api/jobs/auth` — Login (sets cookie)
  - `DELETE /api/jobs/auth` — Logout (clears cookie)
- **Protection:** All `/api/jobs/*` endpoints (except cron) verify auth cookie

### 4.5 Dashboard UI

#### 4.5.1 Login Screen

- Password input with error shake animation
- Matching portfolio dark theme (#0a0a0a background, #64ffda accent)
- Back link to main portfolio

#### 4.5.2 Top Bar (sticky)

- Back arrow to portfolio
- Job Scheduler logo + title
- "Fetch Now" button (manual cron trigger)
- Last cron run timestamp
- Logout button

#### 4.5.3 Stats Bar

- 5 stat cards: Total, New, Saved, Applied, Rejected
- Platform pills with color-coded dots: Indeed (blue), LinkedIn (blue), StepStone (orange)

#### 4.5.4 Filter Bar

- Search input (searches title, company, description)
- Status dropdown: All, New, Reviewed, Saved, Applied, Rejected
- Platform dropdown: All, Indeed, LinkedIn, StepStone
- Sort dropdown: Match Score, Newest, Company, Title

#### 4.5.5 Job List (left panel)

- Card-based layout with:
  - Match score badge (color-coded: green ≥70, yellow ≥50, gray ≥30)
  - Platform indicator dot
  - Status badge
  - Job title (2-line clamp) + company
  - Location, work mode, salary (if available)
  - Discovered time (relative: "2h ago", "3d ago")
  - Matched skills pills (max 5 shown)
  - Quick action buttons on hover (save, reject)
- Pagination: 20 jobs per page

#### 4.5.6 Job Detail (right panel)

- Full job title + company
- Meta: location, work mode, job type, salary
- Match score bar with percentage + label ("Strong match", "Good match", etc.)
- Matched skills pills
- Status action buttons: New → Reviewed → Saved → Applied → Rejected
- "Open Job Posting" button (opens external URL in new tab)
- Notes textarea (auto-saves on blur)
- Full job description (scrollable)
- Footer: discovered date + platform

#### 4.5.7 Responsive Behavior

- Desktop: side-by-side list + detail panels
- Tablet/Mobile: list view, detail opens as full-screen overlay
- Selected card gets highlighted border

